-I was driving by.

17:28.150 --> 17:31.070
Thought I would stop in and say,  "hola."

17:31.080 --> 17:33.090
Hola.  Now what are you really doing here?

17:33.100 --> 17:34.130
-A whiskey.

17:43.170 --> 17:45.030
You framed those thugs for a crime

17:45.040 --> 17:46.070
they couldn't have committed

17:46.080 --> 17:48.040
because they are dead.

17:48.050 --> 17:49.100
I should know, because I shot them.

17:49.110 --> 17:50.200
-Has the mayor got you on speed dial?

17:50.210 --> 17:53.020
-San Toledo's a small town,

17:53.030 --> 17:54.190
and I don't want to be standing too close

17:54.200 --> 17:56.060
when this all blows up in your hands.

17:56.070 --> 17:57.090
-Well, Ortega gave us a choice.

17:57.100 --> 17:59.010
We decided to stay.

17:59.020 --> 18:01.000
Playing fair with him is the best move I got.

18:02.020 --> 18:04.050
The gas station move was reckless,

18:04.060 --> 18:06.000
but it worked.

18:06.010 --> 18:09.010
Ortega wants you sitting at his table at the fight.

18:12.030 --> 18:13.080
See you later.

18:13.090 --> 18:15.170
-Wait, you're forgetting something.

18:15.180 --> 18:17.120
-It's a tuxedo for tonight.

18:17.130 --> 18:19.120
A gift for you from the mayor.

18:19.130 --> 18:21.000
Wear it.

18:21.010 --> 18:22.110
-And how did he know my size?

18:24.080 --> 18:25.080
-He didn't.

18:32.210 --> 18:35.020
-There you are, Charlie boy.

18:35.030 --> 18:36.160
-Well, hello, Vic.

18:36.170 --> 18:38.200
How are you?

18:38.210 --> 18:40.130
-A bit of a busy day, was it?

18:40.140 --> 18:41.150
-Well...

18:41.160 --> 18:44.030
actually, yeah, it was quite--

18:44.040 --> 18:45.230
quite busy.

18:46.000 --> 18:47.120
And, uh, yourself?

18:50.020 --> 18:53.000
-You can't all run around for Ortega.

18:53.010 --> 18:55.110
He's way out of your league, son.

18:55.120 --> 18:57.150
It will end with a bang.

18:57.160 --> 18:59.060
-(iron hisses)

18:59.070 --> 19:01.000
-(scoffs) No.

19:01.010 --> 19:05.000
I wouldn't exactly say we're running around for him...

19:05.000 --> 19:06.060
exactly.

19:06.070 --> 19:07.140
-Well, what would you say?

19:07.150 --> 19:09.000
Exactly?

19:10.050 --> 19:12.220
-Do you think that this might be a conversation you should have with Albert?

19:12.230 --> 19:15.090
-Nah, my son won't listen to me.

19:15.100 --> 19:17.100
I say go left, he turns right.

19:17.110 --> 19:19.200
He's stubborn just like his father.

19:19.210 --> 19:22.050
That's why I'm talking to you.

19:24.200 --> 19:27.120
-And, uh, what do you suggest?

19:28.210 --> 19:30.220
-Well, my approach would be

19:30.230 --> 19:32.210
a little more direct, if you know what I mean.

19:32.220 --> 19:35.110
-Oh, but you can't go after the mayor, Vic, okay?

19:35.120 --> 19:37.170
He's an elected government official, for God's sake.

19:37.180 --> 19:39.220
We'll have every policeman in Spain looking for us.

19:39.230 --> 19:41.190
It's not good for our current situation.

19:41.200 --> 19:43.030
-It's better than being brown bread

19:43.040 --> 19:45.050
in the boot of a Bentley, Charlie.

19:45.060 --> 19:48.100
What happened to Albert's plan of going straight, hmm?

19:50.070 --> 19:51.150
-Look, we're gonna be the mayor's dogs

19:51.160 --> 19:53.050
for as long as he's got us on his leash.

19:53.060 --> 19:55.090
So we make him the mark.

19:55.100 --> 19:57.160
If we can play this right,

19:57.170 --> 19:59.130
we'll get a second chance at the good life.

20:01.030 --> 20:03.030
-What if you get it wrong?

20:04.200 --> 20:06.180
-(tense music)

20:11.200 --> 20:13.110
-That's it, Billy boy. Light on your feet.

20:13.120 --> 20:14.140
Find the sweet spot, that's it.

20:14.150 --> 20:16.000
Start eyeing the line, come on!

20:16.010 --> 20:17.070
Get your rhythm going.

20:17.080 --> 20:19.150
Focus, come on. Hit the sweet spot.

20:19.160 --> 20:21.110
That's good! Jab and move.

20:21.120 --> 20:22.130
-How's he looking?

20:22.140 --> 20:23.160
-Yeah, good.

20:23.170 --> 20:25.060
We had any dough, I'd put in on him.

20:25.070 --> 20:27.030
-More important matters at hand, mate.

20:27.040 --> 20:29.090
-Like what, our friend the mayor?

20:29.100 --> 20:31.110
-And what are we gonna do about him.

20:31.120 --> 20:33.060
Leave it up to the kids to handle?

20:33.070 --> 20:34.090
-Well, it looks like you're not.

20:34.100 --> 20:36.100
-Every breath he takes is an insult

20:36.110 --> 20:37.220
after what he did to my Lily.

20:39.120 --> 20:41.060
-Look.

20:41.070 --> 20:44.060
Why don't you go get yourself ready for the fight?

20:44.070 --> 20:46.020
We could all do with a night out, eh?

20:46.030 --> 20:48.130
-I'm not going.

20:48.140 --> 20:50.180
-What do you mean, you're not going?

20:54.090 --> 20:55.180
-You'll all be there.

20:55.190 --> 20:57.120
Billy will be well supported.

20:58.170 --> 21:00.150
-Oi.

21:00.160 --> 21:02.220
You ain't gonna do nothing stupid, are you, Vic?

21:04.070 --> 21:05.220
-Come on, Hate 'Em.

21:05.230 --> 21:07.090
You know me.

21:12.090 --> 21:13.170
-(mid-tempo music)

21:18.220 --> 21:24.050
-♪ Baby, hold   your head up high ♪

21:24.060 --> 21:28.150
♪ Baby, don't you cry ♪

21:29.200 --> 21:34.160
♪ Let the memories   of this moment go by ♪

21:34.170 --> 21:36.150
-(footsteps approaching)

21:36.160 --> 21:38.200
-Buenos dias,  Lily.

21:38.210 --> 21:39.230
How are you?

21:41.050 --> 21:42.170
-I'm good.

21:42.180 --> 21:44.120
Thanks, Clarence. How are you?

21:44.130 --> 21:47.000
-What could possibly be wrong?

21:47.010 --> 21:49.090
Don't have to be anywhere I don't wanna be

21:49.100 --> 21:52.030
or with anybody I don't wanna be with.

21:52.040 --> 21:53.040
-(Lily chuckles)

21:53.050 --> 21:54.190
Must be nice being you.

21:54.200 --> 21:56.190
-These days it is.

21:58.020 --> 22:01.120
Do you, uh, play poker by any chance?

22:03.190 --> 22:06.130
-Well, I've been known to play a few hands in my time.

22:08.020 --> 22:09.060
-May I?

22:14.160 --> 22:16.020
All right. (clears throat)

22:17.090 --> 22:19.020
-Don't say I didn't warn you.

22:22.040 --> 22:23.100
-(instrumental music)

22:24.180 --> 22:26.060
-Fancy suit.

22:27.180 --> 22:29.130
-Thanks. It was a gift.

22:29.140 --> 22:31.040
-A gift?

22:31.050 --> 22:33.010
From who? -The mayor.

22:33.020 --> 22:34.170
-Why did the mayor get you a suit?

22:34.180 --> 22:36.210
-He wants me sittin' at his table for the fight tonight.

22:36.220 --> 22:39.100
-So he, uh, he bought the gas station shenanigans, then.

22:39.110 --> 22:40.110
-Albert: He did.

22:40.120 --> 22:41.210
And the more he thinks I'm useful,

22:41.220 --> 22:43.140
even loyal, the closer I can get.

22:44.190 --> 22:47.150
-Turn often   while cooking for one hour

22:47.160 --> 22:52.010
or until your rabbit pieces   are nice and tender.  -(chuckles)

22:52.020 --> 22:54.040
Nice and tender rabbit.

22:54.040 --> 22:56.110
-The flesh will cascade   from the bones

22:56.120 --> 22:58.040
in gentle waves...

23:00.040 --> 23:01.080
-Puta!

23:01.090 --> 23:03.110
-(upbeat music)

23:28.100 --> 23:29.220
-(mellow music plays)

23:36.180 --> 23:38.020
-That's five hands in a row.

23:38.030 --> 23:40.010
-I did warn you.

23:40.020 --> 23:41.130
-And I bet no one ever catches

23:41.140 --> 23:43.150
that bottom-dealing move you pulled either.

23:46.060 --> 23:47.220
-Well, I was just making sure

23:47.230 --> 23:49.050
you were paying attention, Clarence.

23:49.060 --> 23:51.110
-Now you have your answer.

23:53.130 --> 23:54.130
-I better get going.

23:54.140 --> 23:56.060
I've gotta get ready for the fight tonight.

23:56.070 --> 23:57.190
-Hey, listen.

23:57.200 --> 24:00.120
I got a regular poker game in town tomorrow.

24:01.230 --> 24:04.190
The two of us could make some money.

24:04.200 --> 24:07.080
-So you're a grifter now, are you, Clarence?

24:07.090 --> 24:09.090
-Isn't there a bit of grifter in all of us?

24:14.210 --> 24:16.090
-(instrumental music)

24:19.130 --> 24:20.220
-Does it fit all right?

24:20.230 --> 24:22.230
-Perfectly.

24:23.000 --> 24:24.110
How does the mayor know your size?

24:24.120 --> 24:25.120
-He didn't.

24:25.130 --> 24:27.100
-But she does.

24:27.110 --> 24:30.020
-Sorry, "she"?

24:30.030 --> 24:32.100
You mean-- you mean the driver who works for the mayor,

24:32.100 --> 24:33.150
who killed the Catalans stone dead,

24:33.160 --> 24:34.200
who we most definitely can't trust?

24:34.220 --> 24:36.020
-That's the one.

24:36.030 --> 24:37.180
-Is she gonna be a problem for you, Al?

24:37.190 --> 24:38.200
-Charlie, don't be silly.

24:38.210 --> 24:39.210
She's in with the mayor.

24:39.220 --> 24:41.090
She's an opportunity, nothing more.

24:41.100 --> 24:42.100
-(phone chimes)

24:43.140 --> 24:45.230
-It's Fanta. Tomas is on the move.

24:46.000 --> 24:47.210
-We'll see you at the fight. -See ya.

24:53.060 --> 24:55.170
-(knocking) -Albert: Billy Boy, you in there?

24:55.180 --> 24:57.050
-Yeah.

25:00.100 --> 25:01.130
(scoffs)

25:01.140 --> 25:03.000
Look at you.

25:04.040 --> 25:05.130
-How you feeling? You all right?

25:05.140 --> 25:06.220
It's a big night.

25:07.230 --> 25:09.220
-Yeah.

25:09.230 --> 25:11.090
Big night.

25:12.120 --> 25:13.120
-What's the matter?

25:16.000 --> 25:18.110
Come on. What's the matter?

25:20.030 --> 25:21.190
-I never really thought I'd get this shot

25:21.200 --> 25:23.070
at a pro fight, you know?

25:23.080 --> 25:24.110
-Mmm.

25:24.120 --> 25:26.040
And yet, here you are.

25:27.200 --> 25:30.140
-Yeah, and what happens if I'm full of shit, hmm?

25:31.200 --> 25:34.050
-Only one way to find out, innit?

25:35.230 --> 25:36.230
I'll tell you one thing.

25:36.230 --> 25:39.020
The answer ain't out there in that soppy sunset.

25:42.230 --> 25:44.100
That's for you, by the way.

25:47.020 --> 25:48.020
-(door closes)

25:52.150 --> 25:54.130
-(up-tempo music)

26:05.050 --> 26:06.190
-(chuckling)

26:13.080 --> 26:15.000
-(rock music)

26:24.160 --> 26:27.090
♪ Rock me, little baby ♪

26:27.100 --> 26:29.230
♪ Say you'll be my girl ♪

26:30.000 --> 26:32.130
♪ Put your feet together ♪

26:32.140 --> 26:35.030
♪ Shake the   whole wide world ♪

26:35.040 --> 26:37.010
-(blows landing)

26:38.020 --> 26:39.130
-You look half decent.

26:41.000 --> 26:43.170
-And who knew all it would take was a good suit?

26:45.200 --> 26:47.050
-(bell dinging)

26:47.060 --> 26:49.050
-(applause) -Albert: Feels empty for a pro fight.

26:49.060 --> 26:52.030
-Ines: The mayor likes to keep things exclusive.

26:52.040 --> 26:53.090
-So where is he?

26:54.100 --> 26:55.100
-Follow me.

26:59.160 --> 27:01.010
-(blows landing)

27:07.040 --> 27:08.060
- Buenas noches , Albert.

27:08.070 --> 27:10.010
-Buenas noches,  Mayor Ortega.

27:10.020 --> 27:11.090
-Sit down and join us.

27:16.140 --> 27:18.150
I hear your friend is the replacement

27:18.160 --> 27:20.100
to fight San Toledo's own son, Rueben Cerro.

27:20.110 --> 27:21.230
-That's right.

27:22.000 --> 27:24.220
-Tell me, how do you rate his chances?

27:24.230 --> 27:27.050
-Well, I wouldn't bet against Billy,

27:27.060 --> 27:29.020
not unless I rigged the fight, of course.

27:29.030 --> 27:31.010
-(Ortega chuckles)

27:31.020 --> 27:32.120
Did you rig this fight?

27:32.130 --> 27:35.210
-San Toledo's not my town.

27:35.220 --> 27:37.010
I wouldn't dream of it.

27:37.020 --> 27:38.100
-(Ortega chuckles)

27:40.040 --> 27:41.160
-Nice and sharp, Billy.

27:45.180 --> 27:47.070
-How's our boy looking?

27:47.080 --> 27:49.070
-About as good as you do, Mrs. H.

27:49.080 --> 27:51.030
-We'll all be out there watching, all right?

27:51.040 --> 27:53.000
We're proud of you, yeah?

27:54.190 --> 27:56.060
Put him on his arse, Billy.

27:58.150 --> 27:59.180
-Alright. You heard her.

27:59.190 --> 28:02.080
Give me four. Good.

28:02.090 --> 28:05.030
-(guitar music plays)

28:16.050 --> 28:18.060
-Pour without fear,  señora.

28:20.130 --> 28:22.020
Gracias.

28:22.030 --> 28:24.000
-De nada, caballero.

28:24.010 --> 28:25.080
-(clapping rhythmically)

28:30.000 --> 28:31.050
-(blows landing)

28:31.060 --> 28:32.060
-(Ortega speaks Spanish)

28:35.020 --> 28:36.020
-Would I be safe in assuming

28:36.030 --> 28:38.040
you know a good bottle of whiskey when you see it?

28:38.050 --> 28:40.020
-I can pick out a blend from a single malt.

28:40.030 --> 28:42.140
-I trust your judgment.

28:42.150 --> 28:44.030
I'll take it neat.

28:44.040 --> 28:47.060
In fact, ask the rest of my guests

28:47.070 --> 28:49.080
what they would like to drink also.

28:56.050 --> 28:58.160
-(instrumental music)

28:58.170 --> 29:00.030
-(construction noises)

29:10.220 --> 29:12.230
-What's he doing, Fanta?

29:13.000 --> 29:15.190
-He's been waiting out on the pier here

29:15.200 --> 29:18.180
for about 20 minutes,  Señorita Lotti .

29:20.210 --> 29:22.090
-(Billy sighs)

29:29.090 --> 29:31.170
-(knocking)  -Cinco minutos,  Billy.

29:31.180 --> 29:33.050
Cerro is a top fighter.

29:33.060 --> 29:36.160
Just try and stay on your feet as long as you can, okay?

29:36.170 --> 29:38.180
-Don't you worry about a thing, mate.

29:38.190 --> 29:41.040
He won't be going down any time soon, okay?

29:41.050 --> 29:42.210
-Right.

29:42.220 --> 29:44.220
-Ponce.

29:44.230 --> 29:47.140
Don't listen to a word he says, son, all right?

29:47.150 --> 29:49.080
You just visualize that win, okay?

29:49.090 --> 29:51.030
Stay focused.

29:51.040 --> 29:52.120
Remember what we spoke about.

29:52.130 --> 29:54.010
Remember the training.

29:55.230 --> 29:57.140
-(rock music)

30:09.170 --> 30:11.090
-(speaking Spanish)

30:22.180 --> 30:25.180
-(speaking Spanish)

30:27.010 --> 30:28.090
-(speaking Spanish)

30:35.230 --> 30:37.210
-(speaking Spanish)

30:48.230 --> 30:50.200
-Excuse us, please.

30:50.210 --> 30:53.020
-(instrumental music)

31:14.080 --> 31:16.080
-Are those the keys from the truck I hijacked?

31:17.090 --> 31:19.050
-It's possible.

